Comment: I find that is a good exercise to manipulate string objects in different languages (and it's accessible to beginners).
I think it's a good idea for a clash, I think that give formula isn't necessarily (because people want to have fun to reflect on).

Goal
* Please simplify the statement. A clash player won't want to spend the time reading a long text just to find it irrelevant to solving the problem.

* Please format "y" and "x" as [[variables]] in the formula.

Input
* Line 1: Please add "[[proposedHeadline]]" after "String".

* Line 2: Please add "[[x]] after "Integer".

Constraints
* Please change "[[proposedHeadline.length]]" to "length of [[proposedHeadline]]" (twice).

* Please do not format "/ 2" as part of a variable.

* The first constraint is violated by "Various characters" (test) and "Various characters 2" (validator). Please revise the constraint and/or the cases.

Thanks.
Thank you so much for the feedback, I corrected all the parts of my contribution. I hope the statement is simplified enough now to not waste clash players' time by making them read unnecessary text.
